[normal]On many occasions people contacting us had not completed their landlord's internal 
[normal]complaints procedure (ICP). In most cases we used to advise completion of the ICP 
[normal]because the. former Scheme provided that, usually, the Ombudsman would not 
[normal]consider complaints which in his opinion could still be pursued through providers' procedures.
[normal]Unde
[normal]r the new Scheme the value that we can add in these circumstances is even 
[normal]greater because I now have the power, at any time, to promote local resolution of a 
[normal]dispute by either referring the complaint back to the complainant and provider and/or a designated
[normal] person; or providing assistance to the complainant and provider and /or 
[normal]a designated person to resolve the dispute.
[normal]Many other cases are outside jurisdiction (OSJ) 
[normal](e.g. 
[normal]the provider may not be a 
[normal]member of the Scheme, or the issue may not relate to a land
[normal]lord and tenant 
[normal]relationship 
[normal]etc) 
[normal]and we may not be able to assist further. Nevertheless, whenever 
[normal]we can, we give information or advice on process and, where possible, signpost people to other agencies that may be able to help them. The table below 
[normal]demons
[normal]trates this activity up to the commencement of my new jurisdiction and our 
[normal]new processes and procedures.
